detaileddescription.para:
defines the number of bad countings of opening contactors at too high current Type:
int Default:
10 Range:
[9,11]

This macro describes the limiting current from the the positive to negative side of the contactor at which a damaging of the contactor occurs. If this limit is exceeded the contacor module makes an entry in the diagnosis module indicating a switching off of the contactors under a bad condition

This macro describes the limiting current from the the negative to positive side of the contactor at which a damaging of the contactor occurs. If this limit is exceeded the contacor module makes an entry in the diagnosis module indicating a switching off of the contactors under a bad condition
